    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-07T12:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-07T12:16:00-05:00" n="844"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/624</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SFJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-07T13:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My November 6, noon. The British Minister informs me that he has been advised by
                    the Minister for Foreign Affairs that he is assured by <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NRS1">Naón</persName> that the Government of
                    the United States not only favored the acquisition by the Argentine Government
                    of the interned German vessels under voluntary contract but had also expressed
                    its willingness to advance the money for the purchase. The Foreign Minister has
                    confirmed this in conversation with me.</p>
                <p>To-day the British Minister has received from the Foreign Office a note
                    indicating that the Argentine Government through the Argentine Chargé d’Affaires
                    in London has formally asked the British Government to recognize the transfer of
                    the flag on the <hi rend="italic">Bahia Blanca</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SFJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
